  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.7.3`\r\nOS & Version: Linux x64\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Question\r\n\r\nHello,\r\n\r\nThere are a lot of new config options in geth, could you please assist us in understanding:\r\n- txpool slots\r\n- cache\r\n- ethash\r\n\r\nWe are running a well connected server with 25GB of ram, and 12 CPU's + SSD. We want a node that can provide web3 to the public, and ideally have a very large TXpool (keep as many transactions in possible in mem).\r\n\r\nCurrently, we have the following settings, can you please provide some suggestions? \r\n```\r\n\"geth\", \\\r\n            \"--port\", \"30303\", \\\r\n            \"--rpc\", \\\r\n            \"--rpcaddr\", \"0.0.0.0\", \\\r\n            \"--rpcport\", \"8541\", \\\r\n            \"--rpcapi\", \"eth,net,web3\", \\\r\n            \"--rpccorsdomain\", \"*\", \\\r\n            \"--ws\", \\\r\n            \"--wsaddr\", \"0.0.0.0\", \\\r\n            \"--wsport\", \"8542\", \\\r\n            \"--wsapi\", \"web3,eth,pubsub,net\", \\\r\n            \"--wsorigins\", \"*\", \\\r\n            \"--datadir\", \"/gethdata\", \\\r\n            \"--txpool.journal\", \"72h0m0s\", \\\r\n            \"--txpool.pricelimit\", \"0\", \\\r\n            \"--txpool.accountslots\", \"429496729\",\\\r\n            \"--txpool.globalslots\", \"4294967295\",\\\r\n            \"--txpool.accountqueue\", \"429496729\", \\\r\n            \"--txpool.globalqueue\", \"4294967295\", \\\r\n            \"--txpool.lifetime\", \"72h0m0s\", \\\r\n            \"--cache\", \"8000\", \\\r\n            \"--syncmode\", \"fast\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n(this is running in the following docker container)\r\nhttps://github.com/go-faast/geth-docker/blob/master/Dockerfile",
